description:
In lichen_peer_remove(), the LOG_INF at line 799 logs eui64[6] and eui64[7] AFTER secure_zero(entry->eui64) at line 797 has already zeroed the entry. The log will always show '..00:00'.

FIX: Move the LOG_INF before the secure_zero calls, or use a local copy for logging:
```c
LOG_INF("lichen_l2: peer removed ..%02x:%02x", eui64[6], eui64[7]);
secure_zero(entry->pubkey, sizeof(entry->pubkey));
secure_zero(entry->eui64, sizeof(entry->eui64));
entry->active = false;
```

Note: the parameter 'eui64' (the search key) still has the original value, so logging eui64[6], eui64[7] from the parameter is correct.
